---
/**
 * context-engineering/0007 · Figure 4 — Module 2 "Flat vs structured retrieval".
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Carries its own <defs> for the arrowhead markers the shared
 * top-of-body <svg> provided in the source.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Flat top-k retrieval returns the matched chunk; small-to-big matches a small chunk but returns its larger parent document."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="160" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Flat: match chunk, return chunk</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Small-to-big: match small, return parent</text
        >

        <!-- flat -->
        <rect x="60" y="40" width="200" height="26" rx="5" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="160" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111110"
            >query &rarr; nearest chunk</text
        >
        <rect
            x="100"
            y="86"
            width="120"
            height="40"
            rx="6"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="103"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">matched chunk</text
        ><text x="160" y="117" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >precise but no context</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="66" x2="160" y2="84" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <text x="160" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >answer often lacks surrounding context</text
        >

        <!-- small to big -->
        <rect x="380" y="40" width="200" height="26" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text x="480" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111110"
            >query &rarr; small precise chunk</text
        >
        <rect
            x="440"
            y="86"
            width="80"
            height="22"
            rx="5"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="101"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">small chunk</text
        >
        <rect
            x="380"
            y="120"
            width="200"
            height="48"
            rx="6"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="139"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">return PARENT document</text
        ><text x="480" y="153" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >precision of small + context of big</text
        >
        <line x1="480" y1="66" x2="480" y2="84" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="480" y1="108" x2="480" y2="118" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        You can decouple <em>what you match on</em> from <em>what you return</em>. Match tiny chunks
        so the embedding is precise, but hand the model the larger parent so it has the surrounding
        context to reason with.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r3">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
